Sterna sparsely setose, cross-impressions visible (Fig. 7E). A rounded subcylindrical sternal process with two small pores between ♂ coxae 4 (Figs 7H, 8G); occasionally a paramedian pair of small, short, rounded tubercles between ♂ coxae 3 as well (Figs 7H, 8F). Legs 1 short, following ones growing increasingly longer and slenderer towards telson, ca 2.2-2.8 (♂) or 2.0-2.2 (♀) times longer than midbody height. ♂ femora 5-7 each with a very strong, rounded, mesal, densely pilose apophysis in distal 1/2 (Figs 7I, 8
